'''German submarine ''U-4711''''' was a [[German Type XXIII submarine|Type XXIII]] [[U-boat]] of [[Nazi Germany]]'s ''[[Kriegsmarine]]'' during [[World War II]]. She was ordered on 7 July 1944, and was [[Keel laying|laid down]] on 1 December 1944 at [[Friedrich Krupp Germaniawerft]] AG, [[Kiel]], as yard number 953. She was [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] on 21 February 1945 and [[Ship commissioning|commissioned]] under the command of ''[[Oberleutnant zur See]]'' Siegfried Endler on 21 March 1945.<ref name="uboat">{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/boats/u4711.htm |title=U-4711 |last=Helgason |first=Guðmundur |website=Uboat.net |accessdate=30 April 2016 }}</ref>
==Design== Like all [[Type XXIII submarine|Type XXIII]] [[U-boat]]s, ''U-4711'' had a displacement of {{convert|232|t|LT}} when at the surface and {{convert|256|t|LT}} while submerged. She had a total length of {{convert|34.14|m|ftin|abbr=on}} ([[o/a]]), a beam width of {{convert|3.02|m|ftin|abbr=on}} (o/a), and a draught depth of {{convert|3.66|m|ftin|abbr=on}}. The submarine was powered by one [[MWM GmbH|MWM]] six-cylinder RS134S diesel engine providing {{convert|575|PS|kW shp|lk=on|abbr=off}}, one [[AEG]] GU4463-8 [[Motor-generator|double-acting electric motor]] electric motor providing {{convert|572|PS|kW shp|abbr=on}}, and one [[Brown, Boveri & Cie|BBC]] [[Silent running (submarine)|silent running]] CCR188 electric motor providing {{convert|35|PS|kW shp|abbr=on}}.<ref name="factory">{{cite web| url=http://www.militaryfactory.com/ships/detail.asp?ship_id=Type-XXIII-Uboat |title=Type XXIII U-Boat Coastal Submarine (1944) |publisher=Military Factory |accessdate=30 April 2016 }}</ref>
The submarine had a maximum surface speed of {{convert|9.7|kn}} and a submerged speed of {{convert|12.5|kn}}. When submerged, the boat could operate at {{convert|4|kn}} for {{convert|202|nmi}}; when surfaced, she could travel {{convert|2600|nmi}} at {{convert|8|kn}}. ''U-4711'' was fitted with two {{convert|53.3|cm|in|abbr=on}} [[torpedo tube]]s in the bow. She could carry two preloaded [[torpedo]]es. The [[Ship's company|complement]] was 14 — 18 men.<ref name="factory" /> This class of U-boat did not carry a deck gun.<ref name="uboat"/>
==Service history== On 4 May 1945, ''U-4711'' was [[scuttling|scuttled]] at Germaniawerft, Kiel, as part of [[Operation Regenbogen (U-boat)|Operation Regenbogen]]. The wreck was later raised and broken up.<ref name="uboat" />
